**Fixing React Type Declaration**

I've just added `import React from 'react';` to the top of `types.ts`. This resolves the "Cannot find namespace 'React'" error on line 29. While `import type { ReactNode } from 'react'` could work, using `React.ReactNode` keeps the code consistent with the original structure. I've ensured the import doesn't cause any conflicts with other parts of the project, especially module declaration. The code should now compile without errors.


